{
  "local_port": 43532,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "To clear your Hotmail inbox, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log into your Hotmail account**: Go to the Hotmail website and sign in with your credentials.\n\n2. **Select emails to delete**: In your inbox, you can select emails one by one by clicking the checkbox next to each email. To select all emails on the current page, click the checkbox at the top of the list. If you want to select all emails in your inbox (even those on other pages), after selecting all emails on the current page, you should see an option that says \"Select all [number] conversations in Inbox.\" Click this to select all emails.\n\n3. **Delete the selected emails**: Once you have selected the emails you want to delete, click the \"Delete\" button (usually represented by a trash can icon). The emails will be moved to the \"Deleted\" or \"Trash\" folder.\n\n4. **Empty the Deleted folder**: To permanently remove the emails, go to the \"Deleted\" or \"Trash\" folder. You can empty this folder by selecting all emails in the same way as described above and then clicking the \"Delete\" button again. Alternatively, some email services offer an \"Empty folder\" or \"Empty trash now\" option; if available, you can use this to clear the folder instantly.\n\n5. **Confirm deletion**: If prompted, confirm that you want to permanently delete the emails.\n\nAfter following these steps, your Hotmail inbox should be cleared. Remember that permanently deleted emails cannot be recovered, so make sure you only delete emails you no longer need.",
